#velvetg 
#increases %CPU in top, takes a bit longer than velveth
#creates a directory 


Output:
        directory/contigs.fa            : fasta file of contigs longer than twice hash length
        directory/stats.txt             : stats file (tab-spaced) useful for determining appropriate coverage cutoff
        directory/LastGraph             : special formatted file with all the information on the final graph
        directory/velvet_asm.afg        : (if requested) AMOS compatible assembly file



-cov_cutoff will allow you to exclude contigs for which the kmer coverage is low(unacceptable poor quality)

-exp_cov give velvetg an idea of the coverage to expect 
MORE INFO AT:https://gituhb.com/dzerbino/velvetk/wii/Manual



time velvetg debruijn_kmer25 -cov_cutoff 1000
Final graph has 86 nodes and n50 of 222, max 655, total 13667, using 0/899534 reads


velvetg debruijn_kmer25 -cov_cutoff 1000 -exp_cov 25000
Final graph has 61 nodes and n50 of 381, max 1147, total 13960, using 846152/899534 reads







